page.title: 04The Old Docks.
page.content: { We went up on the{Itchen Bridge } to look at the view of the{Old Docks.} They had lots of cranes and a few boats. The{docks}are mostly used for business. There was one part which was private. There was a boat in dock but it was not as big as the Leopard or the Dragon which transport you to France.These two ships, until this year sailed from Southampton.We saw a {grain store}behind the smaller boats' funnel.It was a weird building that was grey and had a strange top.We saw the{Southampton Old Bowling Green, } which is the oldest in the world.When we walked past the flower beds we saw{ {an historic building,part of the Old } {Walls,}now a museum.We saw the old church of St. Julien.Behind the church we found the Presbytery.Around the corner was a garage,a snackbar &a pub.
